## Switch placement ##

Switch placement in a bathroom is planned for safety, convenience, and accessibility. Switches for lights, fans, or other electrical devices are usually installed outside wet zones, at least a few feet away from showers, bathtubs, and sinks, to minimize the risk of electric shock. Standard height is typically around 42â€“48 inches from the floor, within easy reach for most users. In some cases, switches may be placed near the entrance or behind doors for convenient control, and using moisture-rated or low-voltage switches in damp areas adds an extra layer of safety. Proper placement ensures functionality while complying with electrical codes and maintaining a safe bathroom environment.